    "WHAT_IS_EPG": [
        {
            "text": "The ethnicity pay gap in the UK refers to the disparity in average earnings between employees from different ethnic backgrounds. According to the Office for National Statistics (ONS), in 2022, Black, African, Caribbean, or Black British employees had a median gross hourly pay of £13.53, compared to £14.35 for White employees. This indicates that Black employees earned approximately 5.7% less than their White counterparts.",
